item.name: Okta Authorization
item.description:
Authorization is done through Okta. Client ID and Secret are provided and will be used to acquire a JWT Token.

**Description:** Makes a request to Okta for a JWT Token.

Clients should encode the provided Client ID and Secrets in Base64 and provide it in the authorization header as **Basic** authorization.

Example:

```
--header 'Authorization: Basic {INPUT_BASE64_ENCODED_CREDENTIALS_HERE}'

```

Replace `{INPUT_BASE64_ENCODED_CREDENTIALS_HERE}` in the Authorization header with the base64 encoding of your client id and secret concatenated around a colon. For example, on Unix systems, this can be achieved with the following shell snippet:

``` shell
export CLIENT_ID="MY_CLIENT_ID"
export CLIENT_SECRET="MY_CLIENT_SECRET"
export BASE64_ENCODED_CREDENTIALS="$(echo -n "$CLIENT_ID:$CLIENT_SECRET" | base64)"
echo $BASE64_ENCODED_CREDENTIALS

```

If successful, they will see the following response:

``` json
{
  "token_type": "Bearer",
  "expires_in": 86400,
  "access_token": "${OKTA_JWT_TOKEN}",
  "scope": "pricing"
}

```

The access token in the response is used in all Client APIs in the authorization header. Be aware that it is a **Bearer** authorization unlike above.

Example:

```
--header 'Authorization: Bearer ${OKTA_JWT_TOKEN}'

```

item.name: Pricing

request.description: **Description:** Gets all configured sources for the client. An array of pricing sources available (based on API keys permissions) will be returned by this endpoint.

**Description:** Get the details for the given pricing source.
Each source object will contain an array of pairs that it supports.

request.description:
**Description:** Gets all configured sources for the client based on a defined product type. An array of sources available, based on API key permissions and inputted product type will be returned by this endpoint.

URL should follow the below format:

https://data-pricing-api.lukka.tech/v1/pricing/sources/details/{productType}

Available Product types include: prices, trades, candles, mvwaps, market-caps, variances

query.description: Specify the type of instrument that is returned. Available options include "spot" and "derivative"
Specify whether to return "active" or "inactive" instruments. Default response will include both active and inactive instruments
Returns all pairs that match the specified Lukka base asset code
Returns all pairs that the match the specified Counter Asset Code

request.description:
**Description:** Get the details for the given product type and specified pricing/market data source ID. Each source object will contain an array of pairs and additional metadata that it supports.

This endpoint will only return the instruments for a given source ID that are permissioined for that specific Client API KEY

URL should follow the below format:

[https://data-pricing-api.lukka.tech/v1/pricing/sources/details/](https://data-pricing-api.lukka.tech/v1/pricing/sources/details/){productType}/{sourceID}

Available Product types include: prices, trades, candles, mvwaps, market-caps, variances

request.description:
**Description:** Get the details for the given product type and specified pricing/market data source ID. Each source object will contain an array of pairs and additional metadata.

This endpoint will only return the instruments for a given source ID that are permissioined for that specific Client API KEY

URL should follow the below format:

[https://data-pricing-api.lukka.tech/v1/pricing/sources/details/](https://data-pricing-api.lukka.tech/v1/pricing/sources/details/){productType}/{sourceID}/derivatives

Available Product types include: prices, trades, candles

query.description: Specify whether to return "active" or "inactive" instruments. Default response will include both active and inactive instruments
Comma delimited list of pair codes. Defaults to all available pair for the source.
Prices as of the given timestamp in UTC. Defaults to now.

Number of milliseconds to lookback for a latest price relative to the asOf date parameter. Default behavior is 172800000 (2 days). 
Minimum value is 1 and maximum value is 31556952000 (1 year)

Specify any additional fields to be displayed in the output response, if available. 
Current values include "partitions" which can be used with Lukka Reference Rate

request.description:
**Description:** Get the price as of the given timestamp from the given pair codes. If pairCodes is left blank, then all pairCodes will be listed for given sourceID.

Keep in mind of the 2048 character limit in a GET request. The pairCodes query parameters should only be used to get a small sub-set of prices. Otherwise use default, which is ALL pairs.

query.description: Comma delimited list of pair codes. Defaults to all available pair for the source.
Prices as of the given timestamp in UTC. Defaults to now.
All prices after or on the given time. Defaults to 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z. Truncated to the minute.
All prices before or on the given time. Defaults to now. Truncated to the minute.
Forward fill gaps in prices with the last known price, if set to TRUE. Defaults to FALSE
Max amount of prices. Defaults to 1440 (1 Day). Max limit is 1440
The Interval that defines the frequency of data within the response object. Current supported values are 60000 milliseconds (1 minute) and 86400000 milliseconds (1 day)

request.description:
**Description:** Get the price history for a single pair.

If the response exceeds the maximum number of records that can be returned in a single payload, then a nextPageUrl field will be returned at the end of the response. The nextPageUrl is used to paginate the response and can be called to request the next batch of records prior to what was returned. nextPageUrl will continue to be included in the response until all of the requested records have been returned.

Prices that are backfilled by previous tick will have an additional filledFrom field. It indicates the price is filled from a previous tick and which tick it is. From this you can determine if it is suitable for your use case.

query.description: All prices before or on the given time. Defaults to now. Truncated to the minute.
Forward fill gaps in prices with the last known price, if set to TRUE. Defaults to FALSE
Max amount of prices. Defaults to 1440 (1 Day)

request.description: Market Capitalization data calculated using Circulating Supply, sourced from Lukka Reference Data, and Lukka Prime minute by minute pricing, leveraging the Lukka Prime Pricing Methodology

query.description: limit of records returned in the response
The as of date for which data will be returned. Defaults to the latest available time if not specified
User specified comma delimited list of pair codes. Defaults to all permissioned pair codes if not specified
Sorting that applies to the rank field in the output. Rank can be ascending (ASC) or Descending (DESC). Defaults to ascending if not specified

request.description: Get a list of the latest Market Capitalization available for a given as of date or given list of pair codes. This endpoint allows users with full permissioned access to see the top coins by market cap historically and on a go forward basis

query.description: comma delimited
asc or desc
All prices after or on the given time. Defaults to 1970-01-01 00:00:00. Truncated to the minute.
All prices before or on the given time. Defaults to now. Truncated to the minute.
Max amount of prices. Defaults to 1440 (1 Day)

request.description:
**Description:** Get the price history for a single pair along with its market variances. For each exchange, daily volume, daily trade counts, hourly volume, and hourly trade counts are provided. Lukka Prime takes all these parameters into consideration when choosing a principal exchange for the minute's price.

Exchanges under market variances are sorted in a descending order by its **hourly volume**.

If the response exceeds the maximum number of transactions that can be returned in a single payload then a nextPageUrl variable will be returned at the end of the response. The nextPageUrl is used to paginate the response and can be called to request the next batch of transactions prior to what was returned. nextPageUrl will continue to be included in the response until all of the requested transactions have been returned.

Max amount of prices. Defaults to 1440 (1 Day)

request.description:
**Description:** Get the 60 minute Volume Weighted Average Price (VWAP) for a given pair code and given Source Exchanges. The VWAP output price for any given timestamp is the volume-weighted price of all executed trades in the previous 60 minutes from the inputted list of Market Data Source IDs that support the requested Pair Code.

If the response exceeds the maximum number of records that can be returned in a single payload, then a nextPageUrl field will be returned at the end of the response. The nextPageUrl is used to paginate the response and can be called to request the next batch of records. The nextPageUrl will continue to be included in the response until all of the requested records have been returned.

Please note the max time range between the to and from parameters should not excceed 7 days

item.description:
**Lukka Pricing Overview** Lukka Pricing & Valuation is an institutional pricing service for crypto valuation and financial reporting. The purpose of this document is to describe how to retrieve Lukka Pricing & Valuation data via the REST API. **For support questions or feedback, please contact your Lukka representative** There are multiple types of data available via the API that can be pulled. Below are descriptions of the endpoints and data types. Notice that each endpoint uses the **GET** command to send a request to the API. The base endpoint that is used to access all data is **https://data-pricing-api.lukka.tech/v1/pricing** and is included in all API calls. All APIs are rate limited by client ID at 5 requests per second. Timestamps are given and recieved as ISO format. Pricing Data Dictionary
Field Name Data Type Description
sourceId INTEGER ID of the pricing source (1000 = Lukka Prime End of Day)
sourceName STRING Name of the pricing source
pairCode STRING Pair code of the priced asset (All tickers and pairs are normalized using Lukka Reference Data)/td>
baseAsset STRING Base asset code of the pair
counterAsset STRING Counter asset code of the pair
pairId INTEGER ID of the paired assets (There's a unique ID for each asset against USD)
firstDate / lastDate TIMESTAMP First date / Last date requested for pricing
pricesCount INTEGER Number of prices
prices LIST Array of prices by timestamp
price DOUBLE Price of the asset
ts TIMESTAMP Timestamp of the price provided
nextPageUrl STRING URL to use for pagination

request.description:
Get a list of all known markets within Lukka that apply to Lukka Marketplace Reference Data ("LMPRD") Lukka Marketplace Data provides information about cryptocurrency marketplaces (i.e. an exchange or other marketplace such as OTC trading desks). The dataset provides its users information about the market type, legal entities, location, applicable regulatory licenses, compliance, certifications, technology, trading details, operating status, successor markets and various information about a marketplace. Marketplaces that are eligible to be tracked within the Lukka Marketplace Reference Data are trading venues where transactions in cryptocurrencies take place. Such transactions include venues where cryptocurrencies, or derivatives of those cryptocurrencies, can be bought, sold, lent, borrowed or swapped for other cryptocurrencies or fiat currencies. Venue types include, but are not limited to: Centralized Exchanges, Decentralized Exchanges, Exchange Aggregators or Relayers, Lending Platforms, Over-The-Counter Desks or Brokers. **Response Details**

Get all known details for a given Lukka Marketplace Identifier from the Lukka Marketplace Reference Data ("LMPRD") Product Lukka Marketplace Data provides information about cryptocurrency marketplaces (i.e. an exchange or other marketplace such as OTC trading desks). The dataset provides its users information about the market type, legal entities, location, applicable regulatory licenses, compliance, certifications, technology, trading details, operating status, successor markets and various information about a marketplace. Marketplaces that are eligible to be tracked within the Lukka Marketplace Reference Data are trading venues where transactions in cryptocurrencies take place. Such transactions include venues where cryptocurrencies, or derivatives of those cryptocurrencies, can be bought, sold, lent, borrowed or swapped for other cryptocurrencies or fiat currencies. Venue types include, but are not limited to: Centralized Exchanges, Decentralized Exchanges, Exchange Aggregators or Relayers, Lending Platforms, Over-The-Counter Desks or Brokers. **Response Details**

request.description:
Lukka Custodian Data provides information about digital asset custodians. The dataset provides its users information about the legal entities, location, applicable regulatory licenses, compliance, certifications, security provisions, operating status, successor entities and other various information about a custodian.

  

Custodians that are eligible to be tracked within the Lukka Custodian Reference Data (LCRD) are custodians that provide custody services for digital assets.

request.description:
The Lukka Reference Data (LRD) product is a comprehensive security master for digital assets. LRD is designed to fulfill the global digital asset communitys need for an institutional-grade, clean, reliable, comprehensive, standardized and normalized data source for digital asset reference data. Furthermore, LRD provides a means to conduct a multitude of digital asset investment activities including: researching trading strategies, quantitative research, benchmark construction, portfolio performance measurement and evaluation, pre and post-trade analysis and risk management assessments.

  

The dataset is comprised of what is commonly referred to as Terms & Conditions in traditional finance. The dataset provides its users information regarding the asset type, the assets structure, participants, how the supply is determined, underlying asset information (if applicable) and other various pieces of reference data. In total, the dataset tracks over 100 fields for its users.

  

Digital assets and derivative products on digital assets are eligible for addition to the Lukka Reference Data product.

item.name: A Lukka Asset and its Details

request.description:
The Lukka Reference Data (LRD) product is a comprehensive security master for digital assets. LRD is designed to fulfill the global digital asset communitys need for an institutional-grade, clean, reliable, comprehensive, standardized and normalized data source for digital asset reference data. Furthermore, LRD provides a means to conduct a multitude of digital asset investment activities including: researching trading strategies, quantitative research, benchmark construction, portfolio performance measurement and evaluation, pre and post-trade analysis and risk management assessments.

  

The dataset is comprised of what is commonly referred to as Terms & Conditions in traditional finance. The dataset provides its users information regarding the asset type, the assets structure, participants, how the supply is determined, underlying asset information (if applicable) and other various pieces of reference data. In total, the dataset tracks over 100 fields for its users.

  

Digital assets and derivative products on digital assets are eligible for addition to the Lukka Reference Data product.

LDRD is designed to fulfill the global digital asset communitys need for an institutional-grade, clean, reliable, comprehensive, enriched, standardized and normalized data source for derivatives on digital assets. request.description:
Get the cross reference of all the assets supported by an entity as a part of the Lukka Mapping Data Product (LMAP)

  

The digital asset ecosystem consists of hundreds of various platforms and service providers, each having their own naming conventions, asset identifiers, notification processes (or lack thereof) and delivery mechanisms (or lack thereof). The absence of standard identifiers across the ecosystem presents challenges to properly identify and compare data across the digital asset ecosystem, especially at scale.

  

The Lukka Mapping Data Product is a comprehensive mapping and normalization dataset that can be leveraged to easily take the unstandardized, inconsistent and uncleansed data from trading venues, custodians, wallets, lending platforms or other entities within the ecosystem and normalize the data to one consistent, standardized, cleansed and timelined data record.

  

LMAP is designed to fulfill the need for a mechanism to facilitate an easy way to compare assets and their respective market data, across any platform, for use in front, middle and back office processes. The product provides its users a significant reduction in time and effort preparing data and provides its users with more time to analyze and use the data.

request.description:
Get the cross reference of all the pairs supported by an entity as a part of the Lukka Mapping Data Product (LMAP)

  

The digital asset ecosystem consists of hundreds of various platforms and service providers, each having their own naming conventions, asset identifiers, notification processes (or lack thereof) and delivery mechanisms (or lack thereof). The absence of standard identifiers across the ecosystem presents challenges to properly identify and compare data across the digital asset ecosystem, especially at scale.

  

The Lukka Mapping Data Product is a comprehensive mapping and normalization dataset that can be leveraged to easily take the unstandardized, inconsistent and uncleansed data from trading venues, custodians, wallets, lending platforms or other entities within the ecosystem and normalize the data to one consistent, standardized, cleansed and timelined data record.

  

LMAP is designed to fulfill the need for a mechanism to facilitate an easy way to compare assets and their respective market data, across any platform, for use in front, middle and back office processes. The product provides its users a significant reduction in time and effort preparing data and provides its users with more time to analyze and use the data.

request.description:
The Crypto Actions endpoint contains information related to the Lukka Crypto Actions (LCA) data product

  

Lukka Crypto Actions is a detailed and comprehensive treatment methodology currently consisting of over 25 Crypto Action Event Types with the purpose of providing firms with data around changes to asset structure and asset characteristics within the digital asset landscape, including structured metadata pertaining to what attributes have changed with an asset, on what date, and as a result of what event.

  

Market events that have material impact on digital assets or are determined by Lukka to be significant in nature are eligible for induction into the assets crypto action history repository. Generally speaking, material impacts revolve around events that affect either an assets protocol structure, characteristics, or reporting in the marketplace. The LCA event types are described in detail in the Structure and Definitions section of this document.

item.description:
**Lukka Reference Data Overview**

Lukka Reference Data is the golden copy of crypto asset reference data. It normalizes and maps thousands of crypto assets from hundreds of sources (entities).

Lukka Reference Data provides comprehensive data for crypto assets, ranging from underlying blockchains and contract addresses to entity-specific tickers, asset names, and asset codes.

Included in the entity-specific details is trade and transfer-level metadata such as price precision, trade and withdrawal fees, and minimum tick size. Lukka Reference Data also provides cross-reference data for assets and asset pairs for cross-entity mapping.

**For support questions or feedback, please contact your Lukka representative.**

There are multiple types of data available via the API that can be pulled. Below are descriptions of the endpoints and data types. Notice that each endpoint uses the **GET** command to send a request to the API.

The base endpoint that is used to access all data is [https://data-refdata-api.lukka.tech/v2](https://data-refdata-api.lukka.tech/v2) and is included in all API calls.

request.description: Lukka's Implied Interest Rate API provides benchmark rates derived from major exchanges, calculated using futures market trade data aggregated hourly. A risk-sensitive model ensures robustness and market representativeness. Term structures are created using Nelson-Siegel-Svenssen (NSS) and Monotone Convex (MC) interpolation methods. This API delivers spot rates and instantaneous forward rates for standardized tenors.

request.description:
Get the cross reference of all the pairs supported by an entity mapped to Lukka normalized pairs.

Response Details
Field Name Data Type Data Type Details Description
entityName CHARACTER 256 Name of the source entity
entityCode CHARACTER 256 Unique Lukka code for the source entity
entityType CHARACTER 20 Type of service provided by the source entity
entityPairCode CHARACTER 256 Pair code provided by the source entity
entityAssetOneCode CHARACTER 256 Base asset code (ticker) of the pair provided by the source entity
entityAssetOneName CHARACTER 256 Base asset name of the pair provided by the source entity
entityAssetOneInternalId CHARACTER 256 Internal code provided by the source entity to uniquely identify the base asset
entityAssetTwoCode CHARACTER 256 Counter asset code (ticker) of the pair provided by the source entity
entityAssetTwoName CHARACTER 256 Counter asset name of the pair provided by the source entity
entityAssetTwoInternalId CHARACTER 256 Internal code provided by the source entity to uniquely identify the counter asset
entityPricePrecision NUMERIC Fixed number of decimal places to which the price is rounded off by the source entity
entityQuantityPrecision NUMERIC Fixed number of decimal places to which the quantity traded is rounded off by the source entity
entityMinimumTickSize NUMERIC Smallest price increment in which the source entity prices are quoted
entityMinimumTradeQuantity NUMERIC Minimum amount of base asset allowed by the source entity to be traded
entityTradeFeeAssetCode CHARACTER 256 Asset code (ticker) of the fee charged by the source entity when trading
entityTradeFeeAmount NUMERIC Amount of fee charged by the source entity when trading
entityTradeFeeType CHARACTER 256 Indicates if the trade fee charged is a percentage or unit
lukkaPairCode CHARACTER 256 Lukka normalized unique pair code
lukkaAssetOneId CHARACTER 11 11-character unique Lukka ID (LID) for the base asset. Please refer to the Lukka ID document for more information
lukkaAssetOneCode CHARACTER 256 Lukka normalized unique asset code (ticker) for the base asset
lukkaAssetOneName CHARACTER 256 Lukka's long name for the base asset
lukkaAssetTwoId CHARACTER 11 11-character unique Lukka ID (LID) for the counter asset. Please refer to the Lukka ID document for more information
lukkaAssetTwoCode CHARACTER 256 Lukka normalized unique asset code (ticker) for the counter asset
lukkaAssetTwoName CHARACTER 256 Lukka's long name for the counter asset
startTime DATE ISO 8601 Timestamp (UTC+0) when the entity pair was mapped to the Lukka pair
endTime DATE ISO 8601 Timestamp (UTC+0) when the entity stopped supporting the pair; also indicates the time when the entity to Lukka pair mapping was removed

request.description:
Get the list of all the contracts supported by an entity.

Response Details
Field Name Data Type Data Type Details Description
entityName CHARACTER 256 Name of the source entity
entityCode CHARACTER 256 Unique Lukka code for the source entity
entityType CHARACTER 20 Type of service provided by the source entity
entityDerivativeCode CHARACTER 256 Code used by the source entity to uniquely identify the contract
entityDerivativeName CHARACTER 256 Additional descriptive information provided by the source entity
startTime DATE ISO 8601 Timestamp (UTC+0) when the derivative contract was listed by the source entity
endTime DATE ISO 8601 Timestamp (UTC+0) for the expiration date of the contract provided by the source entity
settlementTime DATE ISO 8601 Timestamp (UTC+0) for the settlement time of the contract provided by the source entity
instrumentType CHARACTER 256 Type of contract classified by the source entity
instrumentSubtype CHARACTER 256 Additional information on the type of contract
multiplier NUMERIC Value of one point of quoted price in quote currency for one contract. Contract size in futures trading is the amount of underlying asset represented by each futures contract
strike NUMERIC Price at which the put or call option can be exercised
entitySettleAssetCode CHARACTER 256 The asset in which a contract is settled
entityUnderlyingAssetCode CHARACTER 256 The asset making up the contract and upon which the price is based
entityQuoteAssetCode CHARACTER 256 The asset by which a contract is valued
underlyingSymbol CHARACTER 256 Source entity-specific information such as underlying index, descriptive data, unique identifiers, etc.
lukkaDerivativeId CHARACTER 11 11-character unique Lukka ID (LID) for the crypto contract. Please refer to the Lukka ID document for more information
lukkaSettleAssetCode CHARACTER 256 Lukka normalized unique asset code (ticker) for the settle asset. Please refer to the Lukka ID document for more information
lukkaUnderlyingAssetCode CHARACTER 256 Lukka normalized unique asset code (ticker) for the underlying asset. Please refer to the Lukka ID document for more information
lukkaQuoteAssetCode CHARACTER 256 Lukka normalized unique asset code (ticker) for the quote asset. Please refer to the Lukka ID document for more information

request.description:
Get a list of all the crypto actions occurring on an asset.

Response Details
Field Name Data Type Data Type Details Description
event CHARACTER 256 Type of crypto action
eventTime DATE ISO 8601 Timestamp (UTC+0) when the crypto action has taken place or will take place (for future events)
oldLukkaId CHARACTER 11 11-character unique Lukka ID (LID) for the crypto asset before the crypto action event. Please refer to the Lukka ID document for more information
oldWhitepaperAssetCode CHARACTER 256 Ticker of the crypto asset found in the primary source before the crypto action event
oldWhitepaperAssetName CHARACTER 256 Name of the crypto asset found in the primary source before the crypto action event
oldBlockchain CHARACTER 256 Blockchain on which the asset resided before the crypto action event
oldContractAddress CHARACTER 4000 Address of the contract of an asset in its respective blockchain before the crypto action event
newLukkaId CHARACTER 11 11-character unique Lukka ID (LID) for the crypto asset after the crypto action event. Please refer to the Lukka ID document for more information
newWhitepaperAssetCode CHARACTER 256 Ticker of the crypto asset found in the primary source after the crypto action event
newWhitepaperAssetName CHARACTER 256 Name of the crypto asset found in the primary source after the crypto action event
newBlockchain CHARACTER 256 Blockchain on which the asset resides after the crypto action event
newContractAddress CHARACTER 4000 Address of the contract of an asset in its respective blockchain after the crypto action event
newSplitMultiplier NUMBER Change in the balance of the new asset after a crypto action event such as an "Asset Swap" has taken place
eventDetails CHARACTER 4000 Additional information such as a link to the website or publication of the crypto action event

item.description:
**Lukka Reference Data Overview**

Lukka Reference Data is the golden copy of crypto asset reference data. It normalizes and maps thousands of crypto assets from hundreds of sources (entities).

Lukka Reference Data provides comprehensive data for crypto assets, ranging from underlying blockchains and contract addresses to entity-specific tickers, asset names, and asset codes.

Included in the entity-specific details is trade and transfer-level metadata such as price precision, trade and withdrawal fees, and minimum tick size. Lukka Reference Data also provides cross-reference data for assets and asset pairs for cross-entity mapping.

**For support questions or feedback, please contact your Lukka representative.**

There are multiple types of data available via the API that can be pulled. Below are descriptions of the endpoints and data types. Notice that each endpoint uses the **GET** command to send a request to the API.

The base endpoint that is used to access all data is [**https://data-refdata-api.lukka.tech/v1**](https://data-refdata-api.lukka.tech/v1) and is included in all API calls.
